               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-362-person1956">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1956" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1956" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1956" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker, and live in Warner-street, Clerkenwell. On the afternoon of the 10th of July I saw the two prisoners together in Ray-street, Clerkenwell; Marshea had a pair of shoes, tied together with a piece of string; they stopped behind a hearse, and were breaking the string - this gave me suspicion: I told the constable, and he took them.</p>
               <p>ALEXANDER COWAN. These shoes are my property; they were safe at three o'clock on the 10th of July.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-362-person1957">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1957" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1957" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-362-person1957" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was desired by Jones to stop the prisoners: I took the shoes from Marshea, who said his mother sent him to pawn them.</p>
               <p>MARSHEA'S Defence. My mother desired me to take the key to my brother, and as I was returning I picked up the shoes, and tied a handkerchief round them; the officer took me, and I said they belonged to my mother, for fear they should take them from me; they were not tied together.</p>
               <p>McDONALD'S Defence. I saw this lad, who told me he had found the shoes.</p>
               <p>MARSHEA - <rs id="t18280911-362-verdict1871" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-362-verdict1871" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 13.</p>
